				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/buttfranklin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2721810); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2721810&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227537" alt="Buttfranklin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2721810)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/buttfranklin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2721810); return false;" >Buttfranklin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1482871932 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Dec 2016 20:52</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2716165">
									

<p>I've described my visceral — and, I admit, somewhat closed-minded — distaste for the whole GAW enterprise before.</p>
<p>In addition, I'll echo Kalinin's concerns. As far as I'm aware, the title of the previous tale in this series was also some kind of reference to a contentious IRC quote. Let me add a more personal note: come on, Scantron, you're too smart an author — too smart a person — for this silly point-scoring. Aside from the GAW stuff, I really like your writing, and it would make me sad if some muck-slinging led to a decrease in your, or anyone else's, posting frequency.</p>
<p>This piece serves as an ample demonstration of that writing skill I mentioned. With the narratively stifling, largely unrelatable politics stripped away, and the 'lol memes' relegated to a more plausible background role, some great writing comes into play.</p>
<ul>
<li>Brilliant characterisation. You give these IRC nicks distinct, entertaining voices, sometimes in under ten lines of dialogue. You nail the chatroom politics – which is somewhat ironic, given the second paragraph of this comment.</li>
<li>Realistic treatment of reality bending. I can't recall the last time I saw this.</li>
<li>'Look for coincidences' was an inventive, self-aware device.</li>
<li>I hope one day to be able to pace and structure my fiction as well as this. Swapping between different narrators and settings without jarring the flow&#8230; I'd give a more detailed analysis, but I'm not good enough at this sort of thing to know where to begin.</li>
</ul>
<p>However, despite all that, I'm not going to upvote. I hope this doesn't appear childish. My two reasons are firstly, that I dislike the GAW franchise so much that I don't want to support <em>any</em> of its iterations with an upvote, and this one-off success doesn't change that; and secondly, that you've made a deliberate attempt to poison the community with your title, which would be sufficient reason on its own for me to downvote if it weren't for this article's saving graces.</p>

							</div>

								
					
